9 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING EDUCATION LAWS TO LIMIT THE STATE
10 PROMOTION OF TEACHER ATTENDANCE AT MEETINGS OF TEACHER ORGANIZATIONS; PROHIBITING
11 PUPIL-INSTRUCTION-RELATED DAYS FROM BEING USED FOR ATTENDING STATE MEETINGS OF
12 TEACHER ORGANIZATIONS; REMOVING THE MANDATE THAT TRUSTEES CLOSE SCHOOLS FOR THE
13 ANNUAL MEETINGS OF TEACHER ORGANIZATIONS; REVISING ALLOWABLE USE OF PUPIL-
14 INSTRUCTION-RELATED DAYS; AMENDING SECTIONS 20-1-304 AND 20-4-304, MCA; AND PROVIDING
15 AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
18
19 Section 1. Section 20-1-304, MCA, is amended to read:
20 "20-1-304. Pupil-instruction-related day. A pupil-instruction-related day is a day of teacher activities
21 including professional development that is solely devoted to improving the quality of instruction and aligned to
22 standards of the board of public education. The activities may include but are not limited to inservice training,
23 attending state meetings of teacher organizations, and conducting parent conferences. The activities may not
24 include attending state meetings of teacher organizations. A maximum of 7 pupil-instruction-related days may
25 be conducted during a school year, with a minimum of 3 of the days for instructional and professional
26 development meetings or other appropriate inservice training, if the days are planned in accordance with the
27 policy adopted by the board of public education. The days may not be included as a part of the required
28 minimum aggregate hours of pupil instruction."
