2 Section 2. Section 20-4-304, MCA, is amended to read:
3 "20-4-304. Attendance at instructional and professional development meetings. The trustees of
4 a school district shall close the schools of the district for the annual instructional and professional development
5 meetings of teachers' organizations. The trustees of a school district shall close the schools of the district for
6 the annual instructional and professional development meetings of the teachers' organizations meeting the
7 requirements of 20-1-304. A teacher may attend instructional and professional development meetings without
8 loss of salary or attend other appropriate inservice training that may be prescribed by the trustees without loss
9 of salary. If a teacher does not attend, the teacher may not be paid."
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
